g.aria-label: automatic differentiation in C++ couldn't be simpler
automatic differentiation in C++ couldn't be simpler
dual x, y, z; dual u = f(x, y, z); double ux = derivative(f, wrt(x), at(x, y, z)); double uy = derivative(f, wrt(y), at(x, y, z)); double uz = derivative(f, wrt(z), at(x, y, z));
dual3rd x, y; dual3rd u = f(x, y); auto [u0, ux, uxy, uxyx] = derivatives(f, wrt(x, y, x), at(x, y));
real x, y, z; real u = f(x, y, z); double ux = derivative(f, wrt(x), at(x, y, z)); double uy = derivative(f, wrt(y), at(x, y, z)); double uz = derivative(f, wrt(z), at(x, y, z));
real4th x, y, z; real4th u = f(x, y, z); double nx, ny, nz; // direction n = (nx, ny, nz) auto [un0, un1, un2, un3, un4] = derivatives(f, along(nx, ny, nz), at(x, y, z));
var x, y, z; var u = f(x, y, z); auto [ux, uy, uz] = derivatives(u, wrt(x, y, z));

var x, y, z; var u = f(x, y, z); auto [ux, uy, uz] = derivativesx(u, wrt(x, y, z)); auto [uxx, uxy, uxz] = derivativesx(ux, wrt(x, y, z)); auto [uyx, uyy, uyz] = derivativesx(uy, wrt(x, y, z)); auto [uzx, uzy, uzz] = derivativesx(uz, wrt(x, y, z));
